      <dt><%= t("What is the difference between XAMPP for OS X and XAMPP-VM?")%></dt>
      <dd>
        <p>
        <ul>
          <li><%= t("XAMPP for OS X is a native installer for OS X. It installs Apache, PHP and other XAMPP components directly on your OS X system, in the /Applications/XAMPP folder.")%></li>
          <li><%= t("XAMPP-VM is a virtual machine for OS X. It includes Apache, PHP and other XAMPP components and runs them in a Linux-based virtual machine on your OS X system.")%></li>
        </ul>
        </p>
        <p><%= t("For more information, refer to the blog post at %{xampp_vm_blog_url}.", xampp_vm_blog_url: link_to("https://www.apachefriends.org/blog/new_xampp_20170628.html", "https://www.apachefriends.org/blog/new_xampp_20170628.html"))%></p>.
      </dd> 
    
      <dt><%= t("How do I do install XAMPP for Mac OS X?")%></dt>
      <dd>
      <p><%= t("To install XAMPP just do the following:")%></p>
      <ul>
        <li><%= t("Open the DMG-Image.")%></li>
        <li><%= t("Double-click on the image to start the installation process.")%></li></ul>
      <p><%= t("That's all. XAMPP is now installed below the /Applications/XAMPP directory.")%></p>
      </dd>
      <dt><%= t("Does XAMPP include MySQL or MariaDB?")%></dt>
      <dd>
        <p><%= t("Since XAMPP 5.5.30 and 5.6.14, XAMPP ships MariaDB instead of MySQL. The commands and tools are the same for both.")%></p>
      </dd>
      <dt><%= t("How do I start XAMPP?")%></dt>
      <dd>
      <p><%= t("To start XAMPP simply open XAMPP Control and start Apache, MySQL and ProFTPD. The name of the XAMPP Control is \"manager-osx\".")%></p>      
      </dd>
      <dt><%= t("How do I stop XAMPP?")%></dt>
      <dd>
      <p><%= t("To stop XAMPP simply open XAMPP Control and stop the servers. The name of the XAMPP Control is \"manager-osx\".")%></p>      
      </dd>
      <dt><%= t("How can I test that everything worked?")%></dt>
      <dd>
      <p><%= t("Type in the following URL in a web browser:")%></p>
      <p><code>http://localhost</code></p>

      <p><%= t("Now you should see the XAMPP start page.")%></p>
        <%= image_tag "screenshots/xampp-macosx-start.jpg" %>    
      </dd>
      <dt><%= t("Is XAMPP production ready?")%></dt>
      <dd><p><%= t("XAMPP is not meant for production use but only for development environments. The way XAMPP is configured is to be open as possible to allow the developer anything he/she wants. For development environments this is great but in a production environment it could be fatal.")%></p>
      <p><%= t("Here a list of missing security in XAMPP:")%></p>
      <ol>
        <li><%= t("The MySQL administrator (root) has no password.")%></li>
        <li><%= t("The MySQL daemon is accessible via network.")%></li>
        <li><%= t("ProFTPD uses the password \"lampp\" for user \"daemon\".")%></li>
      </ol>
      <p><%= t("To fix most of the security weaknesses simply call the following command:")%></p>
      <p><code>sudo /Applications/XAMPP/xamppfiles/xampp security</code></p>
      <p><%= t("It will kick off a a small security check to make the XAMPP installation secure.") %></p></dd>

      <dt><%= t("What is the meaning of the error messages I see when starting XAMPP?")%></dt>
      <dd>
        <p><%= t("You may get several error messages while starting XAMPP:")%></p>
        <p><code>LAMPP-Apache is already running.<br />
            An Apache daemon is already running.</code></p>
        <p><%= t("The LAMPP startup script did not start XAMPP-Apache because there is an Apache instance already running. To start XAMPP properly, first you have to stop this daemon.")%></p>
        <p><code>LAMPP-MySQL is already running.<br />
            A MySQL daemon is already running.</code></p>
        <p><%= t("This is mostly due to the same reasons as the above error. The LAMPP startup script found a MySQL daemon already running on your system. To start LAMPP properly, you have to stop this daemon first.")%></p>
      </dd>

      <dt><%= t("Apache doesn't seems to start. What can I do?")%></dt>
      <dd>
        <p><%= t("This error can exist for multiple reasons. Apache displays this error under several circumstances. To find the exact reason we have to do some research:")%></p>
        <p><code>tail -2 /Applications/XAMPP/logs/error_log</code></p>
        <p><%= t("If you get any error messages visit %{community} for help.",
               community: link_to(t("our community pages"), "/community.html") ) %></p>
      </dd>

      <dt><%= t("How can I make my XAMPP installation more secure?")%></dt>
